### Test SID Binary Upload + Play (bez wcze≈õniejszego wgrania)
# This sends SID file as binary data via POST (no pre-upload needed)
# Uses: ultimate_play_sid_binary with proper parameters

### Example 1: Play SID from local file
POST http://localhost:8080/
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ultimate_play_sid_binary",
    "arguments": {
      "filePath": "./examples_http/matrix.sid"
    }
  }
}

###
### Example 2: Play SID from base64 encoded data
# First, encode your SID file to base64
# On Windows: certutil -encode music.sid music.sid.b64
# Then copy the base64 content between BEGIN/END markers
POST http://localhost:8080/
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ultimate_play_sid_binary",
    "arguments": {
      "sidDataBase64": "SURBWAE8AAAA..."
    }
  }
}

###
### Example 3: Download SID from URL and play
POST http://localhost:8080/
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 3,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ultimate_play_sid_binary",
    "arguments": {
      "url": "http://example.com/music.sid"
    }
  }
}}

